Working on the weekend like usual… 

I love the way the city feels these days. People are hugging again; smiles are no longer hidden behind masks; events are happening regularly, and normal feels like a possibility.

I hope everyone enjoyed fashion week. Thank you, @officialrondyce, for having me. The collection, the vibes, and the energy were PERFECT.

Walking into the February break EXHAUSTED, EMOTIONALLY DRAINED, OVERWORKED, APPRECIATED, APPRECIATIVE, VALUED, and with a full heart. 

If you know someone who works in education, hug them and buy them a drink.

Shout out to:
1. Someone who got out of bed today even though their depression and anxiety made it nearly impossible. 
2. Someone who’s been trying really hard to love themselves; someone who’s determined to heal. 
3. Someone who actually accomplished something they never thought they would; someone taking steps in the right direction. 
4. Someone who remembered to eat a full meal today, took their medicine, worked out, didn’t self harm, or studied for their test. 
5. Someone who’s been doing what they can to make their dreams a reality; someone who has been actively working towards their goals! 
6. Someone who just doesn’t hear how great they are very often. 
Thank you for still being here! Sometimes, it may feel like your efforts are going unnoticed or that your progress doesn’t matter because it’s slow but that isn’t true! Continue your journey! It won’t all be laughter and sunshine but that’s ok! You will look back on times like this and be thankful that you didn’t give up completely. We’re taking it one step at a time and for that I am proud.
“When you operate from a place of excellence, some will be drawn to it, some will be inspired by it, and others will be intimidated by it.”- @blackgirlsteach

Daily Reminders:

1. You don’t have to be understood or liked by all to be appreciated by yourself. 
2. Love always returns. Maybe it’ll be in a new person, hobby, or environment but it will come back. 
3. Better things exists beyond your current reality. You will experience them. 
4. Stop sharing your good news with people who only suck the energy from you and your excitement. Take your blessings else where. 
5. There is no reward for settling for way less than what you actually want. You are capable of creating the life that you dream of. 
6. Things could be totally different in just a few short months. Stay.
7. Feel your emotions but walk by faith
8. Control how you respond to things sent to disrupt your peace 
9. Being emotionally healthy is attractive 
10. There's always tomorrow

I've been fucking up a lot lately, so I'm intentionally practicing being present, unlearning while learning, being more of the student than the teacher, and taking notes along the way. Here are some of the takeaways from my week:

1. Gratitude is a must
2. This, too, shall past
3. There's beauty in the struggle 
4. Don't hide; deal with your shit
5. A good playlist and outfit will shift ya mood when you're having a bad day
6. There's always tomorrow
7. What's for you will always be for you
8. What's not for you will never be for you
9. Always be yourself
10. Be kind to yourself 
11. Peace is important 
12. Life is hard, but if you surround  yourself with people that make you laugh until you cry, it feels a little lighter
13. The art of listening creates an environment where the other person feels heard.
14. Isolation assists with elevation 
15. Life is a blessing; navigate it accordingly 
16. All the rules are fake, so no matter what, you're not life'ing wrong.
17. Change is fucking scary but so is taking three shots of Henny back to back, and you do that with ease; so you got this.
18. It's okay to cry and be sad, don't stay there too long bc life is waiting for you to live.
19. Everyone's doing their best- give and receive grace.
20. You're doing okay!

Worry less about our garments and more about the current state of education. 

FYI: our videos are made on dress down days 🙄
STOP FIGHTING WITH TEACHERS & EDUCATORS. We deal with enough.

Lessons from my therapist:
▪️Not everyone is supposed to be in your life
▪️Only you can truly hold yourself accountable 
▪️Let your inner child be free
▪️Starting over isn’t hard, it’s brave.
▪️We all need therapy
▪️No matter where you go, be where you are
▪️forgiveness isn’t a feeling – it’s an act
▪️Take people for who they are and not who we want them to be
▪️Show up for yourself with the same urgency and enthusiasm that you show up for others
▪️Trust that what’s meant for you will not pass you
And then God created the Libra ♎️
It all works out the way it's supposed to.

I’m excited to be the Host of Honor for an empowering event designed to uplift and recognize young girls for their accomplishments!
EmpowerHER Year-End Crowning Celebration

The Queen In Me is a Girls Empowerment Organization that aims to provide every girl with the tools and support they need to pursue their dreams fearlessly, overcome challenges, and R.E.I.G.N. while “Becoming the Queen Within!” 

Event: EmpowerHER Year-End Crowning Celebration
Date: Saturday, Dec. 2, 2023
Time: 3:00 PM EST
Venue: First & Main
Address: 315 N First Ave  Knightdale, NC 27545

If you have a special young girl in your life or know of one to invite, you don’t want to miss this experience!
This event will feature motivational speakers sharing their empowering stories, a Crowning Ceremony for all girls, and interactive experiences to build Self-Love, Self-Confidence, and Self-Esteem. This will be a safe and supportive environment to learn, grow, and have fun in an atmosphere that’s Fit For A Queen!

Reserve your tickets now! Seating is limited!

Visit The Website: TheQueenInMe.com
